Figshare API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 2.0.0

Figshare apiv2. Using Swagger, linking with pyramid through pyramid_swagger

Articles

accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDelete

Private Article author remove


/account/articles/{article_id}/authors/{author_id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X delete "http://api.figinternal.dev/v2/account/articles/{article_id}/authors/{author_id}"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ArticlesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ArticlesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long articleId = 789; // Long | Article unique identifier
        Long authorId = 789; // Long | Article Author unique identifier
        try {
            apiInstance.accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDelete(articleId, authorId);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDelete");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Configuration *apiConfig = [Configuration sharedConfig];

// Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: (authentication scheme: OAuth2)
[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

Long *articleId = 789; // Article unique identifier
Long *authorId = 789; // Article Author unique identifier

ArticlesApi *apiInstance = [[ArticlesApi alloc] init];

// Private Article author remove
[apiInstance accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDeleteWith:articleId
    authorId:authorId
              completionHandler: ^(NSError* error) {
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

using System;
using System.Diagnostics;
using IO.Swagger.Api;
using IO.Swagger.Client;
using IO.Swagger.Model;

namespace Example
{
    public class accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDeleteExample
    {
        public void main()
        {
            
            // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
            Configuration.Default.AccessToken = "YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN";

            var apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
            var articleId = 789;  // Long | Article unique identifier
            var authorId = 789;  // Long | Article Author unique identifier

            try
            {
                // Private Article author remove
                apiInstance.accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDelete(articleId, authorId);
            }
            catch (Exception e)
            {
                Debug.Print("Exception when calling ArticlesApi.accountArticlesArticleAuthorsAuthorDelete: " + e.Message );
            }
        }
    }
}

import java.util.*;

        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long articleId = 789; // Long | Article unique identifier
        try {
            array[AuthorPresenter] result = apiInstance.accountArticlesArticleAuthorsGet(articleId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#accountArticlesArticleAuthorsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

accountArticlesArticleAuthorsPost

Private Article authors add

Associate new authors with the article. This will add new authors to the list of already associated authors


/account/articles/{article_id}/authors

        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long articleId = 789; // Long | Article unique identifier
        AuthorsCreator authors = ; // AuthorsCreator | Authors description
        try {
            apiInstance.accountArticlesArticleAuthorsPost(articleId, authors);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#accountArticlesArticleAuthorsPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

accountArticlesArticleAuthorsPut

Private Article Authors replace

Associate new authors with the article. This will remove all already associated authors and add these new ones


/account/articles/{article_id}/authors

accountArticlesArticlePublishPost

Private Article Publish

- If the whole article is under embargo, it will not be published immediatly, but when the embargo expires or is lifted. - When an article is published, a new public version will be generated. Any further updates to the article will affect the private article data. In order to make these changes publicly visible, an explicit publish operation is needed.


/account/articles/{article_id}/publish

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python

        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long page = 789; // Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
        Long pageSize = 789; // Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
        Long limit = 789; // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
        Long offset = 789; // Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
        try {
            array[ArticlePresenter] result = apiInstance.accountArticlesGet(page, pageSize, limit, offset);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#accountArticlesGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ArticlesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ArticlesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long page = 789; // Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
        Long pageSize = 789; // Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
        Long limit = 789; // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
        Long offset = 789; // Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
        String order = order_example; // String | The field by which to order. Default varies by endpoint/resource.
        String orderDirection = orderDirection_example; // String | 
        Long institution = 789; // Long | only return collections from this institution
        String publishedSince = publishedSince_example; // String | Filter by article publishing date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD
        String modifiedSince = modifiedSince_example; // String | Filter by article modified date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD
        Long group = 789; // Long | only return collections from this group
        String resourceDoi = resourceDoi_example; // String | only return collections with this resource_doi
        String itemType = itemType_example; // String | Only return collections with the respective type. Mapping for item_type is: 1 - Figure, 2 - Media, 3 - Dataset, 4 - Fileset, 5 - Poster, 6 - Paper, 7 - Presentation, 8 - Thesis, 9 - Code
        try {
            array[ArticlePresenter] result = apiInstance.articlesGet(page, pageSize, limit, offset, order, orderDirection, institution, publishedSince, modifiedSince, group, resourceDoi, itemType);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#articlesGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

            var publishedSince = publishedSince_example;  // String | Filter by article publishing date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD (optional) 
            var modifiedSince = modifiedSince_example;  // String | Filter by article modified date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD (optional) 
            var group = 789;  // Long | only return collections from this group (optional) 
            var resourceDoi = resourceDoi_example;  // String | only return collections with this resource_doi (optional) 
            var itemType = itemType_example;  // String | Only return collections with the respective type. Mapping for item_type is: 1 - Figure, 2 - Media, 3 - Dataset, 4 - Fileset, 5 - Poster, 6 - Paper, 7 - Presentation, 8 - Thesis, 9 - Code (optional)

                // Public Articles
                array[ArticlePresenter] result = apiInstance.articlesGet(page, pageSize, limit, offset, order, orderDirection, institution, publishedSince, modifiedSince, group, resourceDoi, itemType);
                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }

pageSize = 789 # Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page (optional) (default to 10)
limit = 789 # Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)
offset = 789 # Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit (optional)
order = order_example # String | The field by which to order. Default varies by endpoint/resource. (optional) (default to published_date)
orderDirection = orderDirection_example # String |  (optional) (default to desc)
institution = 789 # Long | only return collections from this institution (optional)
publishedSince = publishedSince_example # String | Filter by article publishing date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD (optional)
modifiedSince = modifiedSince_example # String | Filter by article modified date. Will only return articles published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD (optional)
group = 789 # Long | only return collections from this group (optional)
resourceDoi = resourceDoi_example # String | only return collections with this resource_doi (optional)
itemType = itemType_example # String | Only return collections with the respective type. Mapping for item_type is: 1 - Figure, 2 - Media, 3 - Dataset, 4 - Fileset, 5 - Poster, 6 - Paper, 7 - Presentation, 8 - Thesis, 9 - Code (optional)

    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:

        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {

            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

            var partNo = 789;  // Long | Part Number

            {
                // File upload part information

                Debug.WriteLine(result);
            }
            catch (Exception e)

            }
        }
    }
}

uploadTokenPartNoPut

receives part data

The entire body of the request is piped as-is to S3. It is assumed that the body is the correct piece of the file, from startOffset to endOffset


/upload/{token}/{partNo}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ArticlesApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ArticlesApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ArticlesApi apiInstance = new ArticlesApi();
        Long token = 789; // Long | Token received after initializing an upload
        Long partNo = 789; // Long | Part Number
        byte[] binaryData = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // byte[] | 
        try {
            UploadFilePart result = apiInstance.uploadTokenPartNoPut(token, partNo, binaryData);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ArticlesApi#uploadTokenPartNoPut");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

[apiConfig setAccessToken:@"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN"];

Long *token = 789; // Token received after initializing an upload
Long *partNo = 789; // Part Number
byte[] *binaryData = BINARY_DATA_HERE; // 

ArticlesApi *apiInstance = [[ArticlesApi alloc] init];

// receives part data
[apiInstance uploadTokenPartNoPutWith:token
    partNo:partNo
    binaryData:binaryData
              completionHandler: ^(UploadFilePart output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CollectionsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CollectionsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        CollectionsApi apiInstance = new CollectionsApi();
        Long collectionId = 789; // Long | Collection unique identifier
        try {
            array[AuthorPresenter] result = apiInstance.accountCollectionsCollectionAuthorsGet(collectionId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CollectionsApi#accountCollectionsCollectionAuthorsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CollectionsApi;

import java.util.*;

        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();

        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        CollectionsApi apiInstance = new CollectionsApi();
        Long collectionId = 789; // Long | Collection unique identifier
        AuthorsCreator authors = ; // AuthorsCreator | List of authors
        try {
            LocationPresenter result = apiInstance.accountCollectionsCollectionAuthorsPost(collectionId, authors);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CollectionsApi#accountCollectionsCollectionAuthorsPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

accountCollectionsCollectionPublishPost

Private Collection Publish

When a collection is published, a new public version will be generated. Any further updates to the collection will affect the private collection data. In order to make these changes publicly visible, an explicit publish operation is needed.


/account/collections/{collection_id}/publish

Long *offset = 789; // Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit (optional)

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CollectionsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CollectionsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CollectionsApi apiInstance = new CollectionsApi();
        Long collectionId = 789; // Long | Collection Unique identifier
        Long page = 789; // Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
        Long pageSize = 789; // Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
        Long limit = 789; // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
        Long offset = 789; // Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
        try {
            array[ArticlePresenter] result = apiInstance.collectionsCollectionArticlesGet(collectionId, page, pageSize, limit, offset);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CollectionsApi#collectionsCollectionArticlesGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Long *collectionId = 789; // Collection Unique identifier
Long *page = 789; // Page number. Used for pagination with page_size (optional)
Long *pageSize = 789; // The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page (optional) (default to 10)
Long *limit = 789; // Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)
Long *offset = 789; // Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit (optional)

CollectionsApi *apiInstance = [[CollectionsApi alloc] init];

// Public Collection Articles
[apiInstance collectionsCollectionArticlesGetWith:collectionId
    page:page
    pageSize:pageSize
    limit:limit
    offset:offset
              completionHandler: ^(array[ArticlePresenter] output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

  'page': 789, // {Long} Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
  'pageSize': 789, // {Long} The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
  'limit': 789, // {Long} Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
  'offset': 789 // {Long} Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
};

var callback = function(error, data, response) {
  if (error) {
    console.error(error);
  } else {
    console.log('API called successfully. Returned data: ' + data);
  }
};
api.collectionsCollectionArticlesGet(collectionId, opts, callback);

            var limit = 789;  // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)

collectionId = 789 # Long | Collection Unique identifier
page = 789 # Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size (optional)
pageSize = 789 # Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page (optional) (default to 10)
limit = 789 # Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)
offset = 789 # Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit (optional)

    # Public Collection Articles

curl -X get "http://api.figinternal.dev/v2/collections?page=&pageSize=&limit=&offset=&order=&orderDirection=&institution=&publishedSince=&modifiedSince=&group=&resourceDoi="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CollectionsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CollectionsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CollectionsApi apiInstance = new CollectionsApi();
        Long page = 789; // Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
        Long pageSize = 789; // Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
        Long limit = 789; // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
        Long offset = 789; // Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
        String order = order_example; // String | The field by which to order. Default varies by endpoint/resource.
        String orderDirection = orderDirection_example; // String | 
        Long institution = 789; // Long | only return collections from this institution
        String publishedSince = publishedSince_example; // String | Filter by collection publishing date. Will only return collections published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD
        String modifiedSince = modifiedSince_example; // String | Filter by collection modified date. Will only return collections published after the date. date(ISO 8601) YYYY-MM-DD
        Long group = 789; // Long | only return collections from this group
        String resourceDoi = resourceDoi_example; // String | only return collections with this resource_doi
        try {
            array[CollectionPresenter] result = apiInstance.collectionsGet(page, pageSize, limit, offset, order, orderDirection, institution, publishedSince, modifiedSince, group, resourceDoi);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CollectionsApi#collectionsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Long *page = 789; // Page number. Used for pagination with page_size (optional)
Long *pageSize = 789; // The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page (optional) (default to 10)
Long *limit = 789; // Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)

accountInstitutionHrfeedUploadPost

Private Institution HRfeed Upload

The success response doesn't give much information other than the fact that the system has understood the request, has received the file and has initiated the necessary tasks. There are plans for a way to get more in depth information for the state of the HRFeed Process. The token given in the upper examples is a general figshare API personal token of any of the admins at the institution. No other user should be able to access this endpoint, apart from those given the express permission of uploading HR feeds.


/institution/hrfeed/upload

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.ProjectsApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProjectsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        Long page = 789; // Long | Page number. Used for pagination with page_size
        Long pageSize = 789; // Long | The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
        Long limit = 789; // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query
        Long offset = 789; // Long | Where to start the listing(the offset of the first result). Used for pagination with limit
        String order = order_example; // String | The field by which to order. Default varies by endpoint/resource.
        String orderDirection = orderDirection_example; // String | 
        String storage = storage_example; // String | only return collections from this institution
        String roles = roles_example; // String | Any combination of owner, collaborator, viewer separated by comma. Examples: "owner" or "owner,collaborator".
        try {
            array[PrivateProjectPresenter] result = apiInstance.accountProjectsGet(page, pageSize, limit, offset, order, orderDirection, storage, roles);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#accountProjectsGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

  'pageSize': 789, // {Long} The number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with page
  'limit': 789, // {Long} Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query

  'order': order_example, // {String} The field by which to order. Default varies by endpoint/resource.
  'orderDirection': orderDirection_example, // {String} 
  'storage': storage_example, // {String} only return collections from this institution
  'roles': roles_example // {String} Any combination of owner, collaborator, viewer separated by comma. Examples: "owner" or "owner,collaborator".

            var limit = 789;  // Long | Number of results included on a page. Used for pagination with query (optional)

            var storage = storage_example;  // String | only return collections from this institution (optional)

orderDirection = orderDirection_example # String |  (optional) (default to desc)
storage = storage_example # String | only return collections from this institution (optional)
roles = roles_example # String | Any combination of owner, collaborator, viewer separated by comma. Examples: "owner" or "owner,collaborator". (optional)

try: 
    # Private Projects
    api_response = api_instance.accountProjectsGet(page=page, pageSize=pageSize, limit=limit, offset=offset, order=order, orderDirection=orderDirection, storage=storage, roles=roles)
    pprint(api_response)
except ApiException as e:
    print("Exception when calling ProjectsApi->accountProjectsGet: %s\n" % e)

import io.swagger.client.*;

import io.swagger.client.model.*;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class ProjectsApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ApiClient defaultClient = Configuration.getDefaultApiClient();
        
        // Configure OAuth2 access token for authorization: OAuth2
        OAuth OAuth2 = (OAuth) defaultClient.getAuthentication("OAuth2");
        OAuth2.setAccessToken("YOUR ACCESS TOKEN");

        ProjectsApi apiInstance = new ProjectsApi();
        Long projectId = 789; // Long | Project unique identifier
        ProjectCollaboratorInvite collaborator = ; // ProjectCollaboratorInvite | viewer or collaborator role. User user_id or email of user
        try {
            MessageResponse result = apiInstance.accountProjectsProjectCollaboratorsPost(projectId, collaborator);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling ProjectsApi#accountProjectsProjectCollaboratorsPost");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

accountProjectsProjectDelete

Private Project delete

A project can be deleted only if: - it is not public - it does not have public articles. When an individual project is deleted, all the articles are moved to my data of each owner*. When a group project is deleted, all the articles and files are deleted as well. Only project owner, group admin and above can delete a project. 


/account/projects/{project_id}

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
  • Perl
  • Python
curl -X delete "http://api.figinternal.dev/v2/account/projects/{project_id}"
